snippet: Many on Wall Street agreed that the 175,000 jobs created in May could keep the economy on a steady path but would not  encourage the Fed to let up on its stimulus sooner than expected.
abstract: Investors are trying to make sense of thinking of Federal Reserve chairman Ben S Bernanke, making bets on what they think he sees for economic future; many on Wall Street agree that 175,000 jobs created in May could help keep economy on steady path, but would not encourage Fed to let up on stimulus sooner than expected.
lead_paragraph: Many on Wall Street agreed that the 175,000 jobs created in May could keep the economy on a steady path but would not  encourage the Fed to let up on its stimulus sooner than expected.

headline.seo: Eyes on Fed, Wall Street Ends Higher on Job Data
headline.main: Trying to Divine Intent of Fed, Wall St. Climbs
headline.print_headline: Trying to Divine Intent Of Fed, Wall St. Climbs
